  "original_title": "\u0db7\u0dd6\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0dc5\u0d9f\u0daf\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Crude oil prices to rise soon",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Electricity and Energy Minister Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera said that the price of kerosene will definitely have to be increased by the day after tomorrow.",
        "He said that although kerosene is sold at 87 rupees per liter, it costs the government 420 rupees per liter.",
        "Now by the day after tomorrow, we will definitely have to increase the price of kerosene. We give kerosene at 87 rupees, but it costs us 420 rupees. When they do that, the trade union leaders will take to the streets and say that they will beat the fishermen. On the other hand, they say to give fuel to the people. In order to get the fuel properly, we have to sell what we import at least without any loss and we have to invest that money and import it again. Previously, we had a credit period of about 180 days. I hope to try to raise the money for the ships coming in 08 and 09. Collecting dollars is a challenge as well as collecting rupees."
      ],
